WEBVTT

1
00:00:35.661 --> 00:00:36.662
[Ray] We can't just run.

2
00:00:37.746 --> 00:00:39.081
[sighs]

3
00:00:40.874 --> 00:00:42.167
You got Sherry.

4
00:00:43.210 --> 00:00:45.754
I got Theresa and... [exhales deeply]

5
00:00:46.338 --> 00:00:47.756
...you know. I got Theresa.

6
00:00:48.507 --> 00:00:49.758
Hey. at least we know Philly though.

7
00:00:51.009 --> 00:00:54.388
Now we just gotta put our heads down
and hide everything we love.

8
00:00:55.138 --> 00:00:57.975
[Manny] Yeah. but we don't even
know who's looking for us.

9
00:00:59.226 --> 00:01:01.520
Well. we gonna figure that out. all right?

10
00:01:02.187 --> 00:01:03.522
We'll figure that out.

11
00:01:06.108 --> 00:01:07.109
Hey.

12
00:01:08.151 --> 00:01:09.820
I bet you I can throw mine
further than you.

13
00:01:10.404 --> 00:01:12.447
- [chuckles] Come on. man.
- So stupid.

14
00:01:13.448 --> 00:01:15.867
- And... one...
- You're so stupid. You're so fucking--

15
00:01:15.868 --> 00:01:16.785
...two...

16
00:01:17.578 --> 00:01:18.662
[both] ...three.

17
00:01:35.554 --> 00:01:37.931
{\an8}["Point And Kill" playing]

18
00:02:43.413 --> 00:02:44.456
[music ends]

19
00:02:48.418 --> 00:02:49.877
- [Theresa] Are you high?
- What?

20
00:02:49.878 --> 00:02:52.672
I can't just pick up
and go to Atlantic City. I'm an old lady.

21
00:02:52.673 --> 00:02:55.132
What is you talking about? Atlantic City
ain't nothing but old ladies.

22
00:02:55.133 --> 00:02:56.926
[Theresa]
I'm in the middle of a legal thing.

23
00:02:56.927 --> 00:02:59.011
Oh. yeah? [stammering] What kind
of legal thing? What?

24
00:02:59.012 --> 00:03:01.681
This lawyer I found.
I got to meet with a lawyer tomorrow.

25
00:03:01.682 --> 00:03:03.140
What you need a lawyer for?

26
00:03:03.141 --> 00:03:05.810
I can go down the Shore next week.
thank you very much.

27
00:03:05.811 --> 00:03:07.645
{\an8}No. you can't. Not next week. Nah.

28
00:03:07.646 --> 00:03:09.730
{\an8}The reservation is for tonight.
So you gotta go.

29
00:03:09.731 --> 00:03:11.983
And there's a shuttle. everything.
You gotta go tonight.

30
00:03:11.984 --> 00:03:14.443
What is this? You come in here
with your hair on fire

31
00:03:14.444 --> 00:03:16.320
and I gotta rush off to Atlantic City?

32
00:03:16.321 --> 00:03:18.866
- [Ray sighs] Oh. my God. woman.
- [Shermie whimpers]

33
00:03:19.449 --> 00:03:20.700
- [gasps]
- [grunts]

34
00:03:20.701 --> 00:03:23.452
Do not go through
a woman's closet. Raymond.

35
00:03:23.453 --> 00:03:25.788
Then pack. Please.
Look at this. Isn't this nice?

36
00:03:25.789 --> 00:03:27.331
This is a violation here.

37
00:03:27.332 --> 00:03:30.668
All you do is stay stuffed up inside
with your little scratch cards.

38
00:03:30.669 --> 00:03:32.336
Now. you need to enjoy life.

39
00:03:32.337 --> 00:03:35.756
- But why does it have to be this second?
- Because it's a prize.

40
00:03:35.757 --> 00:03:37.633
You don't cash it in. you gonna lose it.

41
00:03:37.634 --> 00:03:39.886
It's been that long since you won
something? You forgot how prizes work.

42
00:03:39.887 --> 00:03:42.138
- Oh. it's a prize?
- Yeah. a radio prize. A call-in.

43
00:03:42.139 --> 00:03:43.514
Oh. what station?

44
00:03:43.515 --> 00:03:44.974
WMGK.

45
00:03:44.975 --> 00:03:48.311
You know... [singsongy] ...WMGK.
[normal] Yeah. Uh. I had to name a song.

46
00:03:48.312 --> 00:03:51.898
Now. look. you need to go down the Shore
because you deserve it. You hear me?

47
00:03:51.899 --> 00:03:54.108
- I didn't ask for this.
- That's the problem.

48
00:03:54.109 --> 00:03:55.277
You don't ever ask for shit.

49
00:03:55.777 --> 00:03:56.819
Except $10.000.

50
00:03:56.820 --> 00:03:58.029
You know. you're welcome.

51
00:03:58.030 --> 00:04:00.448
- Whatever. [mutters] It's all good.
- I'm not stupid. Raymond.

52
00:04:00.449 --> 00:04:03.701
You and that dopehead. Manny.
think my head's in the sand.

53
00:04:03.702 --> 00:04:06.204
Come on with that. Ma.
Like. what... How about this?

54
00:04:06.205 --> 00:04:08.789
How about you. um.
pack yourself something nice. you know?

55
00:04:08.790 --> 00:04:11.167
'Cause you can probably go see
the Blue Man Group or something like that.

56
00:04:11.168 --> 00:04:12.335
you know what I'm saying? Huh?

57
00:04:12.336 --> 00:04:15.004
Put one of your-your tiger stripe
shirts in there or something. [winces]

58
00:04:15.005 --> 00:04:17.924
[Theresa] Are you dealing dope. Raymond?
Be honest with me.

59
00:04:17.925 --> 00:04:20.468
No. Ma. come on. No. I swear to God.

60
00:04:20.469 --> 00:04:23.429
Actually... Actually.
I'm doing the opposite of that.

61
00:04:23.430 --> 00:04:24.639
The exact opposite of that.

62
00:04:24.640 --> 00:04:26.808
What's the opposite? A charity?

63
00:04:27.684 --> 00:04:29.228
- Yeah. you the charity.
- [Shermie barks]

64
00:04:29.853 --> 00:04:32.522
[Theresa] I paid a fortune
for this retainer. you know.

65
00:04:32.523 --> 00:04:33.689
[growls. barks]

66
00:04:33.690 --> 00:04:36.193
[Theresa] It gives me a headache
to think how much it costs.

67
00:04:36.777 --> 00:04:38.069
- [sighs]
- [Theresa] These people.

68
00:04:38.070 --> 00:04:40.947
they'll take advantage
if you're not watching them every second.

69
00:04:40.948 --> 00:04:43.032
[Ray] Hey. Come on. Come on.
What you doing. hey?

70
00:04:43.033 --> 00:04:44.784
Hey! No. no. You supposed to be packing.
Come on. Hey.

71
00:04:44.785 --> 00:04:47.620
Didn't you hear me. Raymond?
I just paid a retainer

72
00:04:47.621 --> 00:04:50.581
- and I gotta meet with this person!
- All right. wait. Okay. wait.

73
00:04:50.582 --> 00:04:53.543
A retainer? What? What you need a ret...
[breathes heavily]

74
00:04:53.544 --> 00:04:56.045
Is that what the ten G's was for?
A retainer?

75
00:04:56.046 --> 00:04:59.591
You better not tell me that this is
more bullshit for that nig... for my father.

76
00:05:00.551 --> 00:05:01.968
I won't tell you nothing.

77
00:05:01.969 --> 00:05:05.596
Goddamn. Ma. Goddamn. Is that...
Is that what this money was for?

78
00:05:05.597 --> 00:05:07.306
- He's your father.
- Yeah.

79
00:05:07.307 --> 00:05:08.975
Do you have any idea...

80
00:05:08.976 --> 00:05:12.436
God. do you have any idea how much
I've been through to get you that money?

81
00:05:12.437 --> 00:05:14.355
You said the opposite of drugs.

82
00:05:14.356 --> 00:05:17.900
- You're supposed to be painting houses!
- Do you know how terrible the houses are?

83
00:05:17.901 --> 00:05:20.487
- I have to meet with this person. Ray!
- Okay. I'll meet with him.

84
00:05:21.029 --> 00:05:22.989
I'll meet with him. okay?
Text me the place.

85
00:05:22.990 --> 00:05:24.782
Tell the dude
that I'll meet with him. all right?

86
00:05:24.783 --> 00:05:27.994
I mean. my father's guilty as shit.
but I'll meet with his ass. all right?

87
00:05:27.995 --> 00:05:29.829
You're not gonna take it seriously.

88
00:05:29.830 --> 00:05:32.331
I'ma take it so seriously
and I will do whatever it takes.

89
00:05:32.332 --> 00:05:36.795
as long as you pack your shit
so I can take you down to the shuttle.

90
00:05:37.296 --> 00:05:38.714
Atlantic City. baby. What you say?

91
00:05:41.300 --> 00:05:42.301
What song was it?

92
00:05:44.720 --> 00:05:47.181
- What?
- The song. shit-bird.

93
00:05:47.681 --> 00:05:49.057
What song did you name?

94
00:05:49.975 --> 00:05:51.393
- [Shermie growling]
- [scoffs]

95
00:05:51.977 --> 00:05:52.978
[sighs]

96
00:05:55.314 --> 00:05:58.900
[chuckles. sighs]

97
00:05:58.901 --> 00:06:00.152
"Coming to America."

98
00:06:01.361 --> 00:06:02.779
"Coming to America." Neil Diamond.

99
00:06:09.203 --> 00:06:11.830
- I love that song.
- I know you do. I know.

100
00:06:13.582 --> 00:06:14.708
Who's taking Shermie?

101
00:06:17.961 --> 00:06:18.795
[Ray] Shit.

102
00:06:29.097 --> 00:06:31.850
["Church" playing on radio]

103
00:06:35.521 --> 00:06:37.021
[groans] Damn it. Shermie.

104
00:06:37.022 --> 00:06:38.606
I would have pulled over
for you to do that.

105
00:06:38.607 --> 00:06:39.816
You had to do it in here?

106
00:06:41.610 --> 00:06:43.111
[grunting]

107
00:06:47.574 --> 00:06:48.700
[Shermie whines]

108
00:06:51.370 --> 00:06:54.456
- Hey. Hey. stay. You stay.
- [whining]

109
00:07:17.145 --> 00:07:18.855
- [dog barking]
- [doorbell rings]

110
00:07:18.856 --> 00:07:20.815
- [Ray] Hey. [clears throat] Hey.
- [barking. growling]

111
00:07:20.816 --> 00:07:22.149
- [resident] Hey. Come in. Come in.
- Hey.

112
00:07:22.150 --> 00:07:23.442
- All right.
- Enzo. stop.

113
00:07:23.443 --> 00:07:25.528
- He probably-probably smelled my dog.
- [resident] Yeah.

114
00:07:25.529 --> 00:07:27.823
- Enzo.
- [Enzo growls]

115
00:07:30.826 --> 00:07:32.119
[resident] Come here. [kisses]

116
00:07:33.829 --> 00:07:34.954
You hungry?

117
00:07:34.955 --> 00:07:38.291
Uh. No. I'm-I'm all right. I'm all right.

118
00:07:38.292 --> 00:07:39.750
Just in time for breakfast. so...

119
00:07:39.751 --> 00:07:42.795
- [Ray] Mm-hmm.
- [resident speaks Vietnamese]

120
00:07:42.796 --> 00:07:44.755
- Kids. say hi to Ray.
- [Ray] Hey.

121
00:07:44.756 --> 00:07:46.007
- [child 1] Hey.
- [child 2] Hi. Ray.

122
00:07:46.008 --> 00:07:47.968
- Ray. do you want some coffee?
- Only if it's no trouble.

123
00:07:49.344 --> 00:07:50.595
[child 1] She put a curse on you.

124
00:07:50.596 --> 00:07:52.847
[child 2] Mom. she didn't. right?

125
00:07:52.848 --> 00:07:54.640
[all chattering in Vietnamese]

126
00:07:54.641 --> 00:07:56.435
- Fresh.
- [child 2] Stop it.

127
00:08:00.063 --> 00:08:01.190
[chattering continues]

128
00:08:02.065 --> 00:08:03.399
[child 2] Are you insane?

129
00:08:03.400 --> 00:08:04.692
Oh. my God. Mom.

130
00:08:04.693 --> 00:08:06.027
[Ray] Thank you. Thank you.

131
00:08:06.028 --> 00:08:07.779
[child 1] Nobody eats soup for breakfast.

132
00:08:09.114 --> 00:08:10.907
Stop making fun of Grandma.

133
00:08:10.908 --> 00:08:12.700
[child 1] Nobody eats soup for breakfast.

134
00:08:12.701 --> 00:08:14.036
[child 2] Yeah. it's true.

135
00:08:14.912 --> 00:08:17.330
We're the only people
who are crazy in the world.

136
00:08:17.331 --> 00:08:18.582
[Grandma speaks Vietnamese]

137
00:08:19.208 --> 00:08:20.292
[sighs]

138
00:08:22.085 --> 00:08:24.338
[sucks teeth]
That's not aloe vera gel. is it?

139
00:08:25.172 --> 00:08:26.380
Liquid meth.

140
00:08:26.381 --> 00:08:28.759
They dissolve it in here
to smuggle in bulk.

141
00:08:29.343 --> 00:08:32.679
Somebody's gotta convert this to crystals
for the street.

142
00:08:33.429 --> 00:08:37.016
but each spoonful is enough
for a whole hick town.

143
00:08:37.017 --> 00:08:38.808
Yeah. and I couldn't carry half of it.

144
00:08:38.809 --> 00:08:42.230
Bro. it was on the news.
You hit a conversion lab.

145
00:08:42.231 --> 00:08:44.732
You went for a capillary.
you got an artery.

146
00:08:44.733 --> 00:08:48.612
I'll hold on to this for a while.
There's gonna be a lot of heat.

147
00:08:50.364 --> 00:08:51.573
[Ray sighs]

148
00:08:53.450 --> 00:08:57.496
Hey. hey. can these guys...
can... can they find us. Son? Huh?

149
00:08:59.665 --> 00:09:02.041
Who knows what you do. hmm? Other than me?

150
00:09:02.042 --> 00:09:03.252
Nobody.

151
00:09:03.919 --> 00:09:06.004
- But you had this third? Right?
- [sighs]

152
00:09:06.505 --> 00:09:08.005
[Ray scoffs] Rick.

153
00:09:08.006 --> 00:09:10.508
- Where did he come from?
- Well. he got out three weeks ago.

154
00:09:10.509 --> 00:09:12.344
He heard about you on the inside?

155
00:09:13.804 --> 00:09:16.348
And last week. where was he at?

156
00:09:17.558 --> 00:09:20.060
Halfway house? Grandma's?

157
00:09:21.103 --> 00:09:24.565
You know. anybody looking for you.
he's point A.

158
00:09:26.441 --> 00:09:27.818
You get rid of his body?

159
00:09:29.069 --> 00:09:30.903
[Son sighs] Ray.

160
00:09:30.904 --> 00:09:32.072
DNA...

161
00:09:32.698 --> 00:09:34.824
- Dental records...
- Yeah. man. I know. I know.

162
00:09:34.825 --> 00:09:37.952
I know he got teeth. Son.
and I know what cops do.

163
00:09:37.953 --> 00:09:40.788
But I'm-I'm talking
about this-this voice. man.

164
00:09:40.789 --> 00:09:42.874
This voice from the walkie-talkie

165
00:09:42.875 --> 00:09:45.001
and it was one of them fucked-up accents
from up north too.

166
00:09:45.002 --> 00:09:48.254
Like. uh... [New England accent]
..."Larry Bird parked the car in the yard."

167
00:09:48.255 --> 00:09:49.423
[Son] That's pretty good.

168
00:09:51.425 --> 00:09:52.425
This guy saw you?

169
00:09:52.426 --> 00:09:53.635
[normal voice. clicks tongue] No.

170
00:09:55.137 --> 00:09:56.637
Could he just be some tweaker?

171
00:09:56.638 --> 00:09:58.347
No. man. Nah. Son. nah.

172
00:09:58.348 --> 00:10:01.309
The way this dude was talking.
he-he's somebody.

173
00:10:01.310 --> 00:10:04.312
You know... [stammers] ...he's the real deal.

174
00:10:04.313 --> 00:10:06.981
Look. how do I cover my tracks. Son? Huh?

175
00:10:06.982 --> 00:10:09.025
And don't tell me that you don't know.
'cause. you know.

176
00:10:09.026 --> 00:10:11.694
this is basically
the safest place in Philly.

177
00:10:11.695 --> 00:10:14.072
You basically shape-shifted
to get up here.

178
00:10:14.948 --> 00:10:17.950
How long you been at this? Two years?

179
00:10:17.951 --> 00:10:19.744
Not even. Fourteen months.

180
00:10:19.745 --> 00:10:22.413
You couldn't have lasted what.
four months.

181
00:10:22.414 --> 00:10:24.332
if you didn't know
how to keep your head down.

182
00:10:24.333 --> 00:10:26.209
You wasn't saying that shit
when you needed us

183
00:10:26.210 --> 00:10:28.295
to get rid of your competition though.
was you?

184
00:10:37.221 --> 00:10:38.430
Let me show you something.

185
00:10:41.099 --> 00:10:44.811
South Vietnamese. 1975.

186
00:10:46.396 --> 00:10:47.981
Okay. Um.

187
00:10:48.690 --> 00:10:50.149
[clicks tongue. inhales sharply]

188
00:10:50.150 --> 00:10:51.234
What's it worth?

189
00:10:51.235 --> 00:10:53.111
Now? Nothing.

190
00:10:53.695 --> 00:10:58.658
My old man. he left Saigon with. uh.
three million dong. He was rich.

191
00:10:58.659 --> 00:11:02.246
By the time he got here.
these were souvenirs.

192
00:11:03.330 --> 00:11:06.541
Shape-shifting is just called life. Ray.

193
00:11:06.542 --> 00:11:08.919
You can't depend on anything. man.

194
00:11:09.878 --> 00:11:10.963
Hmm?

195
00:11:12.214 --> 00:11:17.302
So that means all you got
is your heart and your wits.

196
00:11:19.471 --> 00:11:20.638
And your family.

197
00:11:20.639 --> 00:11:23.058
- [children laughing. chattering]
- [dog barking]

198
00:11:32.526 --> 00:11:34.111
Go ahead. Keep that shit.

199
00:11:35.237 --> 00:11:38.865
Bro. I came here for your help

200
00:11:38.866 --> 00:11:43.328
and all you gave me was some Kevlar
and worthless dong.

201
00:11:46.456 --> 00:11:48.667
You came here to see a real family. Ray.

202
00:11:50.252 --> 00:11:52.087
Otherwise. you would have come on Monday.

203
00:11:57.259 --> 00:11:58.260
[sighs]

204
00:12:01.388 --> 00:12:05.100
[intercom chatter]

205
00:12:17.279 --> 00:12:18.697
[crying. sniffling]

206
00:12:29.208 --> 00:12:31.042
[groaning] Shit.

207
00:12:31.043 --> 00:12:32.628
[breathing heavily]

208
00:12:40.636 --> 00:12:43.388
[breathing heavily]

209
00:12:44.515 --> 00:12:46.767
[Shermie whining]

210
00:12:55.234 --> 00:12:57.694
[sighs deeply]

211
00:12:59.154 --> 00:13:02.658
Hey. I'll be back.
You guard the house. all right?

212
00:13:05.077 --> 00:13:08.163
[grunting] Shit.

213
00:13:09.957 --> 00:13:11.917
- Fuck. [grunts]
- [Manny] Do you think there's...

214
00:13:12.626 --> 00:13:14.253
You think there's any way we could...

215
00:13:15.796 --> 00:13:17.964
- Can we still give this money back. Ray?
- [laughs]

216
00:13:17.965 --> 00:13:19.549
- Give the money back? Yeah.
- Yeah.

217
00:13:19.550 --> 00:13:22.134
Only if we wanna be standing still
when they kill us. Okay?

218
00:13:22.135 --> 00:13:25.639
[Ray sighing. grunting]

219
00:13:26.557 --> 00:13:27.558
All right.

220
00:13:28.308 --> 00:13:30.227
Hey. look at this. man. Here you go.

221
00:13:31.103 --> 00:13:34.605
[chuckles] You know.
I thought about having a garage sale.

222
00:13:34.606 --> 00:13:36.899
I realized that'd be
the most depressing shit ever.

223
00:13:36.900 --> 00:13:38.734
[Manny] This is probably
the worst garage sale I ever saw

224
00:13:38.735 --> 00:13:40.152
- in my life.
- [Ray] That's what I'm saying.

225
00:13:40.153 --> 00:13:42.405
When my dad went down. Theresa.
she had me. uh.

226
00:13:42.406 --> 00:13:44.073
store all his fucking Lou Rawls and shit.

227
00:13:44.074 --> 00:13:49.120
So I'm gonna put equal share in each bag
and. uh. if anything happen to me...

228
00:13:49.121 --> 00:13:50.663
Come on. man. Hey. hey. hey.

229
00:13:50.664 --> 00:13:54.084
If anything happen to me.
give my share to Theresa. all right?

230
00:13:55.377 --> 00:13:57.295
- I don't like this.
- Come on. man. Can you do that for me?

231
00:13:57.296 --> 00:13:58.922
- Yeah.
- Thank you.

232
00:13:59.673 --> 00:14:01.132
[Ray sighs. sniffs]

233
00:14:01.133 --> 00:14:02.884
- Poor Rick. man.
- Poor Rick. man?

234
00:14:02.885 --> 00:14:05.262
[scoffs] Poor Rick fucked us.
You know that. right?

235
00:14:06.013 --> 00:14:08.139
I mean. did he even know
what was in that house?

236
00:14:08.140 --> 00:14:09.473
Matter of fact. who gave him that tip?

