726
00:46:50.561 --> 00:46:51.478
Are you the lawyer?

727
00:46:53.605 --> 00:46:58.151
I-I'm Michelle Taylor. Sullivan. Whitmore.

728
00:46:59.653 --> 00:47:00.987
Your mother called.

729
00:47:00.988 --> 00:47:02.905
She told me you might not be coming.

730
00:47:02.906 --> 00:47:04.365
I was just heading out.

731
00:47:04.366 --> 00:47:07.160
Yeah. I'm sorry.
I got caught up in traffic.

732
00:47:14.126 --> 00:47:15.127
It's okay.

733
00:47:16.587 --> 00:47:17.588
Let's go inside.

734
00:47:24.469 --> 00:47:25.470
[Michelle] Okay. [sighs]

735
00:47:25.971 --> 00:47:27.264
Come on in.

736
00:47:27.931 --> 00:47:29.391
Uh. just over there.

737
00:47:37.900 --> 00:47:39.109
Please. have a seat.

738
00:47:40.611 --> 00:47:42.320
Uh. are you all right. Mr. Driscoll?

739
00:47:42.321 --> 00:47:44.197
Can I get you a cup of tea? A towel?

740
00:47:44.198 --> 00:47:48.326
Uh. can I get a... a glass of water. please?

741
00:47:48.327 --> 00:47:49.703
- Of course.
- Thank you.

742
00:47:59.838 --> 00:48:00.923
[sighs]

743
00:48:16.438 --> 00:48:17.439
[exhales shakily]

744
00:48:22.861 --> 00:48:24.863
[crying]

745
00:48:30.285 --> 00:48:31.787
[sighs]

746
00:48:38.293 --> 00:48:39.294
[Michelle] It hurts.

747
00:48:41.588 --> 00:48:42.756
I know how hard it is.

748
00:48:46.593 --> 00:48:49.346
[crying]

749
00:48:53.350 --> 00:48:55.602
[crying] Sweet Jesus.

750
00:49:00.482 --> 00:49:01.859
- [whispering] Hey.
- [sobbing]

751
00:49:02.776 --> 00:49:05.112
We are at the mercy of our past.

752
00:49:06.780 --> 00:49:09.825
We push all these feelings down.

753
00:49:10.409 --> 00:49:12.744
Times like this. they surge back up.

754
00:49:13.245 --> 00:49:14.329
I'm sorry.

755
00:49:17.583 --> 00:49:18.750
I'm just. uh...

756
00:49:22.087 --> 00:49:25.381
I'm just...
I'm just worried about something.

757
00:49:25.382 --> 00:49:27.342
[sniffles] Someone.

758
00:49:27.968 --> 00:49:29.136
Of course.

759
00:49:30.554 --> 00:49:33.264
- You love him. No.
- [crying] Oh. Jesus. I'm sorry.

760
00:49:33.265 --> 00:49:35.433
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
- No. no.

761
00:49:35.434 --> 00:49:36.643
It's okay.

762
00:49:37.352 --> 00:49:39.228
Um. [chuckles]

763
00:49:39.229 --> 00:49:41.480
This is good. Really.

764
00:49:41.481 --> 00:49:44.443
You don't know how many people
come in here and put up a wall.

765
00:49:46.069 --> 00:49:49.740
Thank you for-for reminding me
what this is all about. you know.

766
00:49:52.743 --> 00:49:53.994
[Ray] Jesus.

767
00:49:56.163 --> 00:49:57.622
You seem like an honest person.

768
00:49:57.623 --> 00:49:58.957
[crying] Oh. God.

769
00:49:59.791 --> 00:50:00.876
Oh. God.

770
00:50:06.131 --> 00:50:07.382
[breathing heavily]

771
00:50:15.098 --> 00:50:16.807
[sighs. sniffles]

772
00:50:16.808 --> 00:50:20.561
Uh. so. in the past...

773
00:50:20.562 --> 00:50:23.940
[stammers]...
it's been like playing the lottery.

774
00:50:23.941 --> 00:50:27.860
but with COVID.
I think this could be a perfect storm.

775
00:50:27.861 --> 00:50:28.945
Okay.

776
00:50:28.946 --> 00:50:30.989
He's definitely eligible.

777
00:50:31.990 --> 00:50:32.991
Eligible?

778
00:50:33.575 --> 00:50:34.952
For compassionate release.

779
00:50:35.911 --> 00:50:38.746
It may just be
a matter of checking all the boxes.

780
00:50:38.747 --> 00:50:41.458
making sure the paperwork is airtight.
That kind of thing.

781
00:50:43.043 --> 00:50:44.169
Paper... um...

782
00:50:44.711 --> 00:50:46.796
Paperwork. What-What paperwork is that?

783
00:50:46.797 --> 00:50:51.217
From the oncologist.
The bronchoscopy. CT scan.

784
00:50:51.218 --> 00:50:53.262
His cancer is pretty advanced.

785
00:50:53.804 --> 00:50:57.098
but combine that
with a good prison record. which he has.

786
00:50:57.099 --> 00:50:59.184
I... I think we have a real shot.

787
00:51:00.352 --> 00:51:03.772
I can't cure him. Mr. Driscoll.
but I can help get him home.

788
00:51:04.314 --> 00:51:07.401
[grunts] How-How long will this take?

789
00:51:07.901 --> 00:51:12.405
Hmm? This... [chuckles. cries] ...compassion.

790
00:51:12.406 --> 00:51:15.616
Well. the bureaucracy grinds pretty slow.

791
00:51:15.617 --> 00:51:19.328
[chuckles] The good things in life
usually take longer than the bad.

792
00:51:19.329 --> 00:51:22.206
[scoffs] Yeah.
'cause bad is pretty immediate.

793
00:51:22.207 --> 00:51:25.001
[sniffs] Oh. my God.
Them butchers are gonna kill his ass.

794
00:51:25.002 --> 00:51:28.588
Uh. well. we can move him
out of the infirmary first.

795
00:51:28.589 --> 00:51:31.465
Get him to a dedicated wing
at Chester County Hospital.

796
00:51:31.466 --> 00:51:33.551
He'll have a marshal assigned to him.

797
00:51:33.552 --> 00:51:35.178
A marshal? [chuckles]

798
00:51:35.179 --> 00:51:36.596
They gonna put marshals with him.

799
00:51:36.597 --> 00:51:37.681
Yeah. until his release.

800
00:51:38.348 --> 00:51:40.767
- [knocks on table] Yeah.
- Touch wood. [chuckles]

801
00:51:43.187 --> 00:51:44.188
Uh-huh.

802
00:51:47.232 --> 00:51:50.109
Now. I hate this part. but. uh.

803
00:51:50.110 --> 00:51:53.113
Theresa still owes
the rest of the retainer.

804
00:51:56.325 --> 00:51:57.326
I can get you the money.

805
00:51:59.036 --> 00:52:00.037
Okay.

806
00:52:01.622 --> 00:52:03.248
- [Elden's phone rings]
- Oh. shit.

807
00:52:04.917 --> 00:52:06.168
[clicks tongue. sighs]

808
00:52:07.544 --> 00:52:10.338
Now you have gone too far. Mr. Driscoll.

809
00:52:10.339 --> 00:52:12.340
- Uh... Uh. Ray. It's just Ray.
- Ray.

810
00:52:12.341 --> 00:52:14.467
Let me get this straight. Ray.

811
00:52:14.468 --> 00:52:17.429
Your ringtone is "Bat Out of Hell"
by Meat Loaf?

812
00:52:19.973 --> 00:52:21.308
[both chuckle]

813
00:52:23.852 --> 00:52:25.228
Thank you. [laughs]

814
00:52:25.229 --> 00:52:28.064
Thank you. [laughing]

815
00:52:28.065 --> 00:52:32.527
'Cause... 'Cause it's been
driving me fucking insane.

816
00:52:32.528 --> 00:52:34.613
["Bat Out of Hell" playing]
